COMMAND : echo -e "<COLORSTART><TEXTINCOLOR><COLOREND>"

EXAMPLE : echo -e "\e[36mTEXTINGREEN\e[39m"

EXPLANATION :

<COLORSTART>    Sets the color
<TEXTINCOLOR>   This string will be  displayed in the color 
<COLOREND>      Sets the color (If you only want to chnage the color of the string)

ADDITIONAL :

Have a look for all the color codes here :

https://misc.flogisoft.com/bash/tip_colors_and_formatting
